STEPS TO SETUP NODEJS AND JSON SERVER ON LOCAL MACHINE

1. PRE-REQUEST
   A. DOWNLOAD AND INSTALL NODEJS VERSION - https://nodejs.org/en
   B. STUDENT.JSON
   
2. STEPS TO FOLLOW
   A. AFTER INSTALLTION - OPEN COMMAND PROMPT
   B. TYPE - npm install -g json-server (this command would install json server on local machine)
      for MAC OS - sudo npm install -g json-server
   C. Now go to location where student.json file saved on your machine	  
   D. COMMOND TO RUN THE JSON SERVER WITH STUDENT.JSON (DATABASE) --> json-server student.json 
   
======================================================================================================
STEPS TO RUN POSTMAN COLLECTION FROM COMMAND LINE
PRE-REQUEST -
 1. DOWNLOAD POSTMAN CLI -  1. https://learning.postman.com/docs/postman-cli/postman-cli-installation/#mac-apple-chip-installation (BASED ON OS, YOU WILL GET LINK)

1.CLICK ON ... CORRESPONDING TO COLLECTION NAME IN POSTMAN ON LEFT SIDE
2.SELECT RUN COLLECTION
3.SELECTS AUTOMATE RUNS VIA CLI OPTION UNDER FUNCTIONAL ON RIGHT SIDE OF POSTMAN WINDOW.
4.CLICK ON COPY ICON UNDER --> RUN ON POSTMAN CLI
5. TO GENERATE API KEY - CLICK ON ADD API KEY AND INSERT THE KEY 
6. COPY COMPLETE COMMAND BY CLICK ON COPIED OPTION.
7. PASTE THE COMMAND TO CMD AND RUN

============================================================================================================
 
Node.js is mandatory for below commands - generate report in postman with newman from CLI
Install newman from cmd -- goto newman website copy that command and run it on cmd
inorder to run postman collection--> export collection into folder --> navigate to that path and open command prompt
run postman collection in postman = newman run collectionfilename.json
generate report in postman = 
1. npm install -g newman-reporter-html to install package
2. npm newman run collectionfilename.json -r html

then goto folder where collection has exported and check the report.
 
npm install -g newman-reporter-htmlextra   
    